citations:
    citation-agot-daenerys-iv:
        source: source-agot
        properties:
            locator: "Daenerys IV"
            text_from_source: "The Horse Gate of Vaes Dothrak was made of two gigantic bronze stallions, rearing, their hooves meeting a hundred feet above the roadway to form a pointed arch."
            accessed: "2026-03-06"
        notes: "Daenerys and the khalasar arrive at Vaes Dothrak. Viserys earns Dothraki nicknames Khal Rhae Mhar (Sorefoot King) and Khal Rhaggat (Cart King). Ser Jorah discusses Dothraki military capacity. Daenerys gives Viserys gifts of Dothraki clothing; he rejects them and strikes Doreah. Daenerys strikes back. She holds one of her dragon eggs for comfort."
